title: Married At First Sight 2017: runaway bride Lauren moves on with new man
text:
IT SEEMS Married At First Sight’s runaway bride has ran right into the arms of a new man. 
Lauren made headlines after she ditching her husband Andrew in the middle of the night following a drama-free wedding day on the reality series.
And while we won’t hear her side of the story until tonight’s episode, photos posted by the single mum on social media seem to suggest she’s moved on and found love with a new man.
One snap posted on her now-deleted Facebook page in December — just a few months after the wedding episode was filmed — was taken while Lauren was at the airport waiting to board a flight.
“When your boyfriend randomly decides to book a last minute trip,” she captioned a photo of two boarding passes.
The two passes in the photo list the passenger names as “Jake Barnett” and “Lauren Barnett”. The same surname led some people to think the mum-of-one had also married her new fella.
Lauren’s snap of the two boarding passes with the same surname raises questions. Source: Facebook 
Moving on ... it seems Lauren’s found happiness with a new man named Jake. Source: Instagram 
Other snaps posted on Lauren’s Instagram page show her cuddled up with Jake — enjoying dinners and vacations together.
“The Brady Bunch,” one photo was labelled, suggesting Jake has a child of his own. Another was hashtagged “my man”.
“The Brady Bunch” ... a photo of the pair out to dinner with the kids suggests he’s a single dad. Source: Instagram 
A snap Lauren posted on Instagram shows the pair holidaying in January. Source: Instagram 
A source told New Idea this week the single mum was happy the reality TV marriage ended because it allowed her to return to Jake, whom she met a few weeks prior to the wedding.
“She is blissfully happy with him — he is a lovely guy, very settled and really looks after her,” the friend told the publication.
